<dl id="n36041e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36041e">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36041e"> 41(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> chihari chatah</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Formerly the greatest ornament of the city was the arcaded and roofed bazaar called <i><mark>Chih&acirc;r Ch&acirc;t</mark>&acirc;</i>, ascribed to Ali Mardan Khan, a noble of the 17th century, who has left behind him many monuments of his munificent public spirit both in Kabul and in Hindustan. <small> &ldquo;KABUL&rdquo; <a name="EBKA" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBKA"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 624d-625a</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
